Cape Town - The Adams family in Macassar is devastated as Brendon Adams, 32, has been missing since Sunday. His wife, Rheilmondia Adams, says Brendon was last seen travelling home from Zevenwacht in Kuils River in his white Opel Corsa. She says he had communicated that he was safe while travelling but he never made it home. Rheilmondia admits they had a “normal couple’s argument” before Brendon left on Saturday morning. He is 1.6m tall, and was wearing denim jeans, denim shirt, white adidas sneakers, a gold watch and a silver necklace. He has a scare on his forehead a tattoo on his right hand and on his right wrist, a name “Mashak” and stars on both wrist. Brendon’s disappearance has devastated his 27-year-old wife, son aged 5 and a 1-year-old daughter. “I want to ask everyone if you know his whereabouts please contact me. I, the kids, family and friends are worried. And my husband wherever you are please come home, we need you and hope you’re safe,” pleads the wife. Rheilmondia describes him as a spontaneous person. “If you see him and met him for the first time, he’s an open book, talks a lot and has a fun character.” He has missed out on their third-month anniversary. She reported him missing at Macassar SAPS on Monday afternoon. The provincial police spokesperson, Captain FC van Wyk says: “Missing Brendon Cameron Adams was reported at Macassar SAPS, investigations continues. According to reports, on Saturday morning, the missing person 32-year-old Brendon Cameron Adams, left his house in Macassar to family members in Kuils River.“ Anyone with information on his whereabouts is urged to call Rheilmondia on 060 725 7413, or the investigating officer Detective Sergeant Delport on 021 857 7100 and or the Crime Stop on 08600 10111. Weekend Argus